{
  "text": "Then we experience in this seeming difficulty the what I would call effect of the wisdom of the first distortion. And for that reason must fully accept the wisdom of that which we experience. This is my personal view. Is it congruent with Ra's? I am Ra. In our view, we would perhaps go further in expressing appreciation of this opportunity. This is an intensive opportunity in that it is quite marked in its effects of both actual and a potential, and as it affects the instruments, the distortions towards a pain and other difficulties such as the dizziness. It enables the instrument to continuously choose to serve others and to serve the creator. Similarly, it offers a continual opportunity for each in the group to express support under more distorted or difficult circumstances of the other self experiencing the abrunt, shall we say, of this attack, and thus being able to demonstrate the love and light of the infinite creator and a furthermore choosing, working by working to continue to serve as messengers for this information which we attempt to offer and to serve the Creator thereby. Thus the opportunities are quite noticeable as well as the distortions caused by this circumstance.",
